Hi, let me introduce myself.

My name is Gloria. I used Claude to design this website, and I thought I could give a little testimony. Claude is an AI assistant made by Anthropic. My brother Max introduced me to it because I told him I wanted to create a website for my writing. Yes, I love writing.

Over the years, I have wondered about many ways to share my faith. I tried almost everything, but nothing seemed to last. I always ended up putting my own desires first and losing the sense of the message. But with writing, I just need a pen and paper — or in this case, my laptop.

This evening, I was watching an EWTN documentary about Saint Pier Giorgio. At such a young age, he became a witness of Christ through his love of prayer, care for the poor, and passion for climbing. After finishing the documentary, I realized that I do not quite have the qualifications to be a saint — but God can make me one if I choose to be His witness.

I started thinking about my passions: photography, filming, singing, speaking. I wondered what comes naturally to me, something I can spend hours doing. Besides talking, I truly love writing. This morning, I even thought about seeing whether I had a talent for composing songs, but I ended up writing a six-page story booklet instead. It became obvious that songwriting is probably not my gift.

So, in this day and age, how do I share my writing? I am not on Instagram, TikTok is not really for me, and neither is Substack. So I wondered if I should create my own website. Since printing costs me a lot, and because many young people are accessible through their phones, I decided that this would be the best way to reach them.

Now, about my friend Claude — I do not know if it was because I was a new user, but every time I tried creating a website, I could only use  Claude for about twenty minutes before it told me I had reached the limit on the free plan and needed to wait eight hours. This went on for days, and eventually I gave up because I did not have the time to wait.

But this evening, while reflecting on serving the Lord with the gifts of the holy spirit and deciding to focus on writing, I thought about Claude again. I told myself I would try one more time, and if it did not work, that would be fine — I would simply continue with my day.

Tell me how I ended up spending the next four hours building a website from scratch. From one page to another, with countless prompts, restarting over and over again, until finally it was done. And tell me the Lord was not in the room while all of that was happening.

At any moment, things could have gone wrong or completely stopped there is so much steps that i am pretty sure Claude got tired of me  plus I am not even a programmer, yet here I am writing on this platform.

I know it may sound simple. You might think, “Gloria, that’s just AI. There’s no faith lesson in that.” But let me tell you something, If it was not him you wouldn't be reading this right now, i give you 4 hours to create a website , well it might be easy for you, but it is not for me.  

Yet God made a way for me. He opened the door, and here I am.

So I thank You, Lord, for Your presence. You do not reveal Yourself only in the great moments, but also in the ordinary things, in the moments where we think something is impossible, yet You are there.

Guide me with Your wisdom so that I may share my faith with others in ways that glorify You, O Lord. Praise and glory be to You, Lord Jesus Christ, now and forever.

So welcome to Sodales Caeli — Latin for “Companion of Heaven.”

Let us keep our baptismal vows by being witnesses to the true Lord and helping one another on the journey to Heaven. and remember to see Christ even in the little that you have.

God bless.